the legend of the white serpent ( 白夫人の妖恋 byaku fujin no yoren ) aka madame white snake is a 1956 color ( eastmancolor ) japanese film directed by shirō toyoda .   at the 6th berlin international film festival it won the honourable mention ( colour ) award .   this film was made by toho ( japan ) in collaboration with the shaw brothers ( hong kong ) .   it is a film adaptation of the traditional chinese legend the legend of the white snake ' as well as fusao hayashi 's story , " madam white 's witchcraft " .   it is a film adaptation that takes pieces of both stories and combines them .   the second half of madame white snake with her son , xu mengjiao , is omitted , as well as the subplot with the tortoise monk , fahai , who in this version , is just a taoist monk who exhibits selfishness disguised as selflessness .